@acjones

Every time you think a puzzle is abysmal and you wonder how it ever passed muster, consider that perhaps you missed something. NYT puzzles sometimes have small errors, but are never as bad as you think this one was. 

And before you embarrass yourself in a public forum, read the column and other comments to understand why it makes sense, even if you didn’t get it in the first place.

